CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER - JAPAN (08): DOMESTIC, WILD, SPREAD
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 31 Aug 2019
Source: AfluDiary.Blogspot [abridged, edited]
http://afludiary.blogspot.com/2019/08/japan-maff-39th-farm-outbreak-of.html


1. Japan's MAFF reports the 5th classical swine fever (CSF) farm outbreak for August 2019, bringing the country's total to 39 farms since the virus re-emerged -- after an absence of 26 years -- just shy of a year ago. While Gifu Prefecture remains the epicenter of this outbreak, we've seen not only a geographic expansion, but an acceleration of outbreaks over the past few months.

2. It took Japan more than 5 months (164 days) to report their 1st 10 farm outbreaks, but we've seen that number nearly quadruple since mid-February [2019], with 29 new outbreaks over the past 191 days.

3. Summary of the wild boar surveillance (as of 14 Aug 2019):

-Gifu prefecture (since 13 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 1914 wild boars (368 dead and 1546 captured), Positive: 841 (275 dead and 566 captured)
-Aichi prefecture (since 14 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 797 wild boars (36 dead and 761 captured), Positive: 65 wild boars (16 dead and 49 captured)
-Nagano prefecture (since 14 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 212 wild boars (89 dead and 123 captured), Positive: 59 (29 dead and 30 captured)
-Mie prefecture (since 14 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 131 wild boars (15 dead and 116 captured), Positive: 4 (0 dead and 4 captured)
-Fukui prefecture (since 14 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 39 wild boars (5 dead and 34 captured), Positive: 7 (0 dead and 7 captured)
-Toyama prefecture (since 14 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 29 wild boars (9 dead and 20 captured), Positive: 4 (3 dead and 1 captured)
-Other 37 prefectures (since 14 Sep 2018). Tested (RT-PCR): 352 wild boars (265 dead and 87 captured), Positive: 0

[Byline: Michael Coston]

